INFJ - the counselor
You scored 36% I to E, 47% N to S, 28% F to T, and 50% J to P!
Your type is best summed up by the word "counselor", which belongs to the larger group of idealists. Only 2% of the population share your type. You are so empathic that you often know what others need before they know themselves. You are a complex person who can deal with complicated issues and people, almost prefer to, as you love problem solving. You can be something of an idealist or perfectionist, and should try to take yourself a little less seriously.
You are a supportive and insightful romantic partner, encouraging your mate to have dreams and work hard to make those dreams come true. Because you are so creative, you have a wealth of ideas to help them toward those goals. You need harmony so much that you are driven to resolve conflict quickly, as long as the terms don't violate your ethics. You feel the most appreciated when your partner admires your creativity, trusts your inspirations, and respects your values. It is also vitally important that your partner be open and emotionally available - in other words, that they be willing to share themselves completely.

So yesterday something amazing happened on the way to my Art Appreciation class.  As I was going to enter the McAulich Arts Center, a guy sitting on a bench next to the door asked me, "Hey, do you want to be in a zombie movie?"  Of course I said yes, but I had to take my final first.  So after my final, the guy wasnt where I had seen him...but just off in the distance down the hallway I saw some people with grey faces.  The hunt was on!

     I followed them to one of the three interior courtyards of the IC (where most of the classes are).  There were already about 5 other zombies there, along with two non-zombies.  I then met this guy named Calvin, who was one of two directors as well as the main character.  I said that i wanted to be a zombie, so he took me to a bathroom and applied makeup on me, mostly grey with black pockets around the eyes and mouth.  Then we went back, and I changed into something that I could get bloodied up (as they had some extra shirts).  Then I proceeded to get bloody. First I applied some makeup-style blood from a little tube to my goatee and neck.  Then Calvin added some red food coloring to some Karo syrup, and we applied it liberally to our clothes, hair, whatever.  I took some im my mouth and spit it all over.  It was amazing.  It looks like real blood, too.

     Once we were all made up and blooded up, we were told where to stand in the courtyard for the scene.  The movie itself is about this guy who, on the way to his dealer, gets sent to a demon world/universe/dimension thingy, and has to fight his way out.  The way COD is built, it is easy to find places that look very industrialistic for the filming process, so I think it will turn out nicely.  Oh, and since the main character has no weapons, he must fight the zombies using what he has: kung fu.  The zombies are led by this demon leader, but I wasnt in any of those scenes.  Anyways, we were all standing in the courtyard.  We had to memorize our positions for consistency in the shots.  What happened was there are two doors in this courtyard (the entire thing is actually like a hole in the middle of the building, with four walls in a square around a simple grassy...grass.  Thing.)  Calvin runs out of one door and across the green, fighting the zombies off.  What was cool was that since im a bigger guy, I could stay up more, so he did this cool move where (since my arms were up in zombie-like fashion) he knocked my arms to the side and then started pummeling my chest, finally taking me down somehow.  It was friggin sweet.  We fimed that along with some detailed shots and some random getting hit shots, and then we went for one more location where Calvin had to run down this pathway and he ran into some zombies, so he has to run right through them (they/we) are in a tight line.  we changed clothes with each other so as to not be the same zombies.  It was awesome.

      Luckily, one of the zombies had a camera, so we took a group photo at the end.  Calvin told me that he really enjoyed working with me (kinda a cliche, i guess, but hell, it was friggin sweet) and he said he'd let me know of his next projects.  I told him that i was going to UofI next semester (to which he replied, "Chambana"? which was cool), but I said if i was home, id let him know.  I got his phone number as well as the girl with the camera, so hopefully I will get both a copy of the movie so we can all watch it (at least paulin and I) and some of the pictures.  That was by far the sweetest random thing to happen to me at COD.

I Am A: Lawful Good Elf Ranger Fighter

Alignment:
Lawful Good characters are the epitome of all that is just and good. They believe in order and governments that work for the benefit of all, and generally do not mind doing direct work to further their beliefs.

Race:
Elves are the eldest of all races, although they are generally a bit smaller than humans. They are generally well-cultured, artistic, easy-going, and because of their long lives, unconcerned with day-to-day activities that other races frequently concern themselves with. Elves are, effectively, immortal, although they can be killed. After a thousand years or so, they simply pass on to the next plane of existance.

Primary Class:
Rangers are the defenders of nature and the elements. They are in tune with the Earth, and work to keep it safe and healthy.

Secondary Class:
Fighters are the warriors. They use weapons to accomplish their goals. This isn't to say that they aren't intelligent, but that they do, in fact, believe that violence is frequently the answer.

Deity:
Mielikki is the Neutral Good goddess of the forest and autumn. She is also known as the Lady of the Forest, and is the Patron of Rangers. Her followers are devoted to nature, and believe in the positive and outreaching elements of it. They use light armor, and a variety of weapons suitable for hunting, which they are quite skilled at. Mielikki's symbol is a unicorn head.

Today was my day off.  What did I do?  More importantly, lets set things straight.  I have no skill when it comes to starting a LJ entry.  None.  No creativity, nothing.  Oh, I'm fine writing after I start, but the first crucial lines fail me.  Which is also the largest stumbling block in my latest endeavor, writing my Personal Statement for my UIUC application.  I have no clue where to begin, or how to write it.  Last time I just used my national merit scholar essay which was a load of horse shit.  The thing is, this could determine a great deal of my future...in this one 700-800 word essay.  Good news, though, on the rest of the application, the lowest GPA to get into LAS is only 2.7, and I have a 3.288 right now (with one F).  So perhaps I'll do fine.  Also I will have a 2 year degree, so that always looks good.

On the personal front, I've had to battle savage (;D) attacks on my personality and how I socialize...but hey, everyone knows I'm a nerd, so I was able to straighten things out.  For the record, I'm terrible at deciding which person or group of friends to hang out with if given the choice.  And also I dont enjoy group activities with people that I've lost a lot of respect for even though they used to be a good friend, and people that...well, I'm not going to start anything.  If I've excluded people, I apologize, I know how much I'd hate it if I did the same

Well isn't that depressing enough.  Oh yeah...today was my day off.  I went to the 3rd day of classes, only to find that my art appreciation class was canceled, so I had time to order a transcript at COD as well as talk to Ms Snyder at NCHS about getting a transcript there.  After that I putzed around on the written UIUC app and then took a nap.  Around 6 or so I went to Zach's to fix my brakes from setting off the brake light, the short term solution being to add more break fluid.  Wow, what a day.

Well, it is official, you all have left Naperville, with Lauren leaving a few days ago.  Shows how often I update this thing.  But my point is, its just not the same.

For example, tonight at around 11:30, the need for a slurpee rose in me, and took over my bodily actions.  However, there wasnt anyone else to share the urge with, so in an effort to save face at the 7-11 and more importantly to my inner ego, I had to recruit Trevor to go with me.  On the one hand, thats the kind of brother to brother bonding shit that we will look back on and say "wow, remember when we were speaking to each other?".  On the other hand, thats kinda lame, having to take your younger brother to 7-11...I wish you guys were back here.  Plus I could have been talked into a few Jr Bacon Cheeseburgers. 

Fortunately, Labor Day is fast approaching, and soccer practice shall ensue.  And what ever happened to making a soccer practice video? And aslo Halo?  And also some more MST3K, it kinda died towards the end of summer.

Which reminds me, its kinda funny how by the end of summer all of us had paired up.  When Ed and Lauren FINALLY got together, and then more abruptly when Annie and Dan got together, group activities started to dwindle.  Not like any of us minded, except maybe Mike, beacause Acey wasnt always around.  But I would like to suggest a MST3K get together at some point this weekend, perhaps Sunday (?)  Now, I know not all members will be around, but a few will.  And thats better than nothing but Wischweh calling every damn night nagging me to do "something" which usually means "think of something to do, Kyle" which either turns into me playing computer games by myself or us going to Meijer.  Damn, I wish you guys were around.  Or I was around you guys.  Yeah, more of the latter and less of the former.

Well, I think I went full circle there.  Glad to see you stuck around to the end of the post, I really appreciate it.  Until next time, fellow LJ'ers.

Wow.  Anyone who has a computer good enough to run it should be playing it.  Of what do I speak? Only the coolest, scariest, most innovative, graphically excellent, most in-depth first person shooter since Half-Life.  Thats right kiddies, Doom 3 is out as of 8/4.  So if im on the computer, chances are I'm playing it.  For those of you who cant run it, you're welcome over to watch me play anytime.  I'd write more, but there's hellbeasts to frag.

Ever sit in front of the computer, staring at a blank entry field, wondering what to write?  If so, then thats what I'm going through right now.  If not, then howsabout you writing something for me? Like, for example, a better attempt at a joke than that last part.  And also aviod the self-pity, it gets to be rather pathetic.

Oh, on an update on the whole working thing, the day after I told my boss that I was leaving in 2 weeks (the Sunday before last, to be exact), we had a discussion after work.  It amounted to him asking what kind of a raise I thought was fair, so I said $7.00/hr (a $1.00 raise, which goes to show you why I was leaving in the first place), and also I get from this past Sunday till this coming Monday, more than a week.  And weekends off in the future.  I think what happened was that he realized that if I were to leave, he would be, to quote Snatch, "proper-fucked". 

So, its good to know that I'm wanted.  Oh, and Six Flags was great.

And my 19th birthday is this Thursday.


And Manos: The Hands of Fate is terrible.

I decided to quit working at Spokes.  Its a good job and all, but I for one need some free time, and flexibility on weekends.  I also have only had one raise in 2 years, and it wasnt looking like another one was coming any time soon...the same thing with the others that work there.  Plus I need a change of pace, something that allows me to 1. Do something other than work with bikes, 2. Lets me have the opportunity for advancement, and 3. Gives me more money.



In other news, riots broke out as local resident Kyle Hagen refused to go see a drive-in movie at the nearby theater in Aurora last evening. Hagen was quoted as saying "it looked like rain, I had already seen both the movies, and I never like turning down MST3K".  Sources say that the "drive-innians" placed an expletive filled phone message on Hagen's voice mail, the contents of which have not yet been released to the press.  When reached for comment, Hagen stated "I simply didnt think it was that big of a deal.  Some people need to chill out."  None of the rioters could be reached for further comment.

I've noticed that recently most people dont comment nearly as much on entries as they usually do.  I dont have that much time to be bored at the computer, and when I do I try to play games, not so much to post on LJ.  I guess it's just a result of Summer...now we arent putting off homework by going online etc.

It's been awhile since I last posted, so I figure I should update.  Not much has changed since last entry, Im still procrastinating on the assassins idea, I'm still in school and I will be until late August-ish.  Right now I'm waiting around for my Meterology class to start at 1:00, just having been in Comparitive Religions.  On Mondays and Wednesdays I have those two classes, from 10 to 4.  It's going to be a fun summer.  On the plus side, T-Th I take speech at the naperville campus, so thats not too bad.  And fortunately on Fridays I dont have either school OR work.  That will definitely feel nice.

Lets see, what else...happy birthday to Ed, now give me the damn Cracklin' Oat Bran.  That stuff is more addicting than heroin, and it tastes better, too.  We definitely need to keep up the MST3K'ing throughout the summer, that among a few things is keeping me going.


Oh, and about that assassins game, I either need some motivation or some help in organizing it, I'm finding that between work, school, and hanging out I have little to no time to organize it.

And awhile back I updated my picture as you all noticed, I think it makes me look more psychotic but less like a pedophilic serial rapist.

I still plan on doing it, I'm going to wait for everyone who wants to play to get home (mainly at this point the General and Rachael).  I think I'm going to have a smaller group play, at least for the first round, maybe around 20 people or so.  Let me know if you guys have any ideas.

I figured its time to update the journal.  I dunno if im going to organize assassins, ive got a lot of stuff going on, what with class and work and everything.  Who knows.  In any case, I need feedback.

Right now I'm on maybe 4.5 hours of sleep.  Steak and Shake last night was good, but odd...it was me, Ed, and Lauren, and we happened to run into Laura.  So unfortunate, she's so evil.  And a bitch.  Ed did all he could to keep from taking his rage out on her, very commendable.  Then later, after Laura thankfully left, we all spooned each other.

This morning I woke up at 6:30 so I could get to COD when the Library opened to write my business paper.  I succeded, and hopefully I'll do well like last time I did the same thing (I got 100% on the paper, by the way).  Then I found out I got a 90 on the test I took on Friday.  Whew.

Thats all for now, folks

Last night was really fun.  First it was just going to Ed's to nerd out on Halo, but then I got hungry and decided to see if Alyson and Annie wanted to come along for food and coffee.  The plan was Panera, but it was after 10, and I think they closed even earlier than that.  So we made Wendy's work...mmm, classic triple. So much beef.  Oh, I guess we didnt go for coffee, but it was late anyways and we didnt know of too many places open (and we werent in the mood for steak and shake).

So instead we went back to Ed's and played some Halo (where Ed beat all 3 of us, but I dont care, on any computer FPS I would kick his ass, he can have his console victory), then watched Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back.  Fun times.  The highlight of the evening was the clips at the end: Judd Nelson in "Lets Go Back To The Station House".  like...lets go back to the station house... and round up some drunks and cornhole them; ...circle jerk, glaze some doughnuts; ...for some man chowder; ... and blow each other.  Amazing.
